<html>
<head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <title>Forms, love em!</title>
</head>
<body>
    <a href="samWeb.html">Back</a>
    <h1>FORMS</h1>
    <p>Forms are elements that are used to collect user input from the website and send it to a server.
    Input is typically gathered from the &lt;input&gt;
        Note in order to use reserved characters such as &lt;, you have to use entity references. Which typically reference the specific character in between a &amp; and &semil; symbol
    </p>
    <form>
        <!--Forms are used for putting input tags together within the form tag -->
        <ul style="list-style-type:none">
            <!-- the 'style' attribute references a block of css code 
                anything within the qoutes, is a block of css. In the above, I set the list-style-type key to 'none', which will hide the bullet points for my forms-->
            <li><label for ="fname" ><b>FIRST NAME</b></label></li>
            <li><input type="text" id="fname" required/></li>
            <li><b>Last Name</b></li>
            <li><input type="text" /></li>
            <li><b>Password</b></li>
            <li><input type="password" /></li>
            <li><b>Email</b></li>
            <li><input type="email" /></li>
            <li><b>Age</b></li>
            <li><input type="number" /></li>
            <li><b>Birthday</b></li>
            <li><input type="date" /></li>
            <li><input type="submit" value="Submit" /><input type="reset" value ="Reset" /></li>
            <li><input type="checkbox" name="mycheckbox" value="dog" />Dog</li>
            <li><input type="checkbox" name="mycheckbox" value="cat" />Cat</li>
            <li><input type="checkbox" name="mycheckbox" value="tyranosauras bobbert" />T-bobbert</li>
        </ul>

        <li>
            <input type="radio" name="toolbarReminder" value ="hourFromNow" />Hour from Now
            <input type="radio" name="toolbarReminder" value ="tomorrow" />Tommorrow
            <input type="radio" name="toolbarReminder" value ="Every Day" checked="checked" />Every Day
        </li>
        <li>
            <h4>Favorite Ice Cream</h4>
       <select>
           <option>Select Option</option>
           <option>Vanilla</option>
           <option>Chocolate</option>
           <option>Bing Tool Bar</option>
       </select>
            
        </li>

    </form>
    <hr />
    <h3>Formatting
    </h3>
    <p>There exist various formats you can apply to text using tags.</p>
    <ul>
        <li><b>Bold Text</b></li>
        <li><i>Italizied Text</i></li>
        <li><u>Underline Text</u></li>
        <li><s>strike though</s></li>
        <li><q>hello</q></li>
        <li><em>Emphasized</em></li>
        <li><mark>Highlighted</mark></li>
    </ul>
    <!--With checkboxes you first indiciate which textboxes are grouped together. This is done with 'name' tag. Value indicates which value each text box represents, -->
</body>
